body:
## What changes were proposed in this pull request?

Cluster creation fails when installing ONEFS via blueprint.

```
Logical Request: Provision Cluster 'cc' FAILED: Unable to update configuration property 'fs.defaultFS' with topology information. Component 'NAMENODE' is mapped to an invalid number of host groups '0'.
```

## How was this patch tested?

tested with the following blueprint

```json
{
  "host_groups" : [
    {
      "name" : "host_group_1",
      "components" : [
        { "name" : "ZOOKEEPER_SERVER" },
        { "name" : "ONEFS_CLIENT" },
        { "name" : "ZOOKEEPER_CLIENT" }
      ],
      "cardinality" : "1"
    }
  ],
  "Blueprints" : {
    "stack_name" : "HDP",
    "stack_version" : "3.0"
  }
}
```
